    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1881-02-25T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1881-02-25T00:00:00-05:00" n="191"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d191">
                <head>No. 191.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">
                        <persName type="from">Chen Lan Pin</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to"
                            >Evarts</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Chinese Legation</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1881-02-25">
                            <hi rend="italic">February</hi> 25, 1881</date>. (Received February
                        25.)</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I had the honor on the 21st ultimo to send your
                    excellency a communication upon the subject of the riot at Denver, Colo., which
                    resulted in the loss of life and the destruction of property owned by the
                    Chinese residents.</p>
                <pb facs="0459" n="335" xml:id="pg_335"/>
                <p>I shall be greatly obliged, Mr. Secretary, if I may soon receive a reply thereto,
                    that I may communicate the same to my government.</p>
                <p>Accept, sir, the renewed assurance of my highest consideration.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>CHEN LAN PIN.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
